{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7f5ccf90-1922-4f9f-a814-f5d4e5c207a1","content":"Here's what you need to change:\n\n### 1. Update packages in your `.csproj`\n\n**Remove:**\n- `NUnit3TestAdapter` (4.6.0)\n- `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`\n\n**Add:**\n- `NUnit3TestAdapter` **5.0.0+** (has built-in Microsoft.Testing.Platform support)\n\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"NUnit3TestAdapter\" Version=\"5.0.0\" />\n```\n\n### 2. Update project properties\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n- **`OutputType Exe`** — the test project now runs as a standalone executable.\n- **`TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`** — enables `dotnet test` compatibility with the new platform.\n\n### 3. Running tests\n\nTests still run via `dotnet test`, or you can run the test executable directly:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test            # works with the property above\n./bin/Debug/net8.0/MyTests   # direct execution\n```\n\n### Key notes\n- Your **NUnit test code stays the same** — no source changes needed.\n- NUnit3TestAdapter 5.0+ ships the MTP integration; the older 4.6.0 only supports VSTest.\n- If you need VSTest **and** MTP side by side during migration, you can keep `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` temporarily alongside the v5 adapter.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2ac14694-a731-4f49-a2d9-ab4b734823a6","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a general knowledge question — I don't need to explore any codebase. Let me provide a concise answer.\n\nKey changes needed for migrating NUnit from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n1. Replace `NUnit3TestAdapter` with `NUnit.Runner` (the Microsoft.Testing.Platform runner for NUnit)\n2. Replace `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` with the new platform packages\n3. Update the project file\n4. Update how tests are run\n\nLet me think about this more carefully. The migration path for NUnit to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n\n- Remove the old `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` and `NUnit3TestAdapter` packages\n- Add `NUnit.Runner` which brings in Microsoft.Testing.Platform as a dependency\n- Change the project to output as an executable by setting `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>`\n- Optionally enable `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>` to maintain compatibility with `dotnet test` commands\n\nThe NUnit team created `NUnit.Runner` specifically as the adapter for this new platform, though I should double-check the exact package name and version requirements. I'm uncertain about the exact package name for NUnit's Microsoft.Testing.Platform integration, but the general migration pattern is clear—I need to add a property like `<UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>true</UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>` to the project file to enable it.\n\nThe key is upgrading `NUnit3TestAdapter` to version 5.0 or later, which includes native MTP support, or alternatively using a dedicated extension package. I'll provide the most straightforward answer based on what I know about the documented migration path.","outputTokens":1401,"requestId":"7034:1A4FD7:E202067:F835501:69F2A769"},"id":"c18b7d79-47f5-416d-9876-76808aaf9e93","timestamp":"2026-04-30T00:51:17.089Z","parentId":"c6f3832b-4318-4fd4-9511-69d4b58ef64c"}
